President Obama addressed the nation in a press briefing after the bombings in Boston. He expressed his condolences to the victims and their families, and stated that the FBI is investigating the attacks as an act of terrorism. The President emphasized that the American people refuse to be terrorized and highlighted the acts of heroism and kindness that were witnessed in the aftermath of the bombings. He assured the public that the government will take appropriate security measures to protect the American people and urged citizens to report anything suspicious to authorities. The President praised the response of law enforcement agencies and the leadership of Governor Patrick and Mayor Menino. He concluded by stating that more information will be shared as it becomes available.